msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 3. Udāyivagga → bodhanā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Udāyivagga "
msgstr "3. With Udāyī "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21. Bodhāyasutta → udāyīvaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn46.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Bodhāyasutta "
msgstr "21. To Awakening "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn46.21:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn46.21:2.1"
msgid "“‘Bojjhaṅgā, bojjhaṅgā’ti, bhante, vuccanti. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of the ‘awakening factors’. "

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti? "
msgstr "How are the awakening factors defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.21:2.3"
msgid "“‘Bodhāya saṃvattantī’ti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā bojjhaṅgāti vuccanti. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, they’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening. "

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhu, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "A mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.5"
msgid "‘Bodhāya saṃvattantī’ti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti. "
msgstr "They’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.21:2.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

